Visualisation of gene set enrichment analysis using GOplot

Anna Jaeschke
Twitter: @anna_jaey
Github: anna-jaey

19/08/2020

Task

  • MS/MS data set (protein expression)
  • small sample set

Gene Set Enrichment analysis

Gene Set Enrichment Analysis (GSEA) is a computational method that determines whether an a priori defined set of genes shows statistically significant, concordant differences between two biological states (e.g.phenotypes). https://www.gsea-msigdb.org/gsea/index.jsp

  1. gene expression data (transcriptome, proteome) - MS/MS Data set
  2. differential gene expression between groups of interest (log2FC)
  3. gene set enrichment & gene set clusters
  4. visualisation

Database for Annotation, Visualization and Integrated Discovery (DAVID)

https://david.ncifcrf.gov/

Webservice

require(RDAVIDWebService)

Bioconductor package

BiocManager::install('RDAVIDWebService')

Gene set enrichment

library(GOplot)
library(tidyverse)
library(stringr)

david<-DAVIDWebService$new(email = "user@example.com",
                           url =  'https://david.ncifcrf.gov/webservice/services/DAVIDWebService.DAVIDWebServiceHttpSoap12Endpoint/' )
setAnnotationCategories(david, c('GOTERM_CC_FAT', 'GOTERM_MF_FAT', 'GOTERM_BP_FAT', "UP_KEYWORDS"))

addList(david, dep$Accession, idType = "UNIPROT_ACCESSION", listName = 'DEP 1.75', listType = 'Gene')
addList(david, dep15$Accession, idType = "UNIPROT_ACCESSION", listName = 'DEP 1.5', listType = 'Gene')
setCurrentGeneListPosition(david,1)

fct.annot <- getFunctionalAnnotationChart(david, threshold = 0.1)
# getFunctionalAnnotationChartFile(david, fileName = filename, threshold = 0.1)

GOplot

annot_df <- data.frame(
  ID = str_split_fixed(fct.annot[["Term"]], "~", 2)[,1],
  category = fct.annot[["Category"]],
  term = str_split_fixed(fct.annot[["Term"]], "~", 2)[,2],
  count = fct.annot[['Count']],
  FoldEnrichment = fct.annot[["Fold.Enrichment"]],
  genes = fct.annot[["Genes"]], 
  adj_pvals = fct.annot[["Benjamini"]]
  )

## GO Terms only
go_data <- circle_dat(annot_df, dep[,38:39])
go_df <- go_data[go_data$category %in% c('GOTERM_MF_FAT', 'GOTERM_CC_FAT', 'GOTERM_BP_FAT'),]
go_df$category<-str_split_fixed(go_df$category, "_", 3)[,2]

Functional Annotation Clustering

cluster.annot <- getClusterReport(david, overlap=4L, initialSeed=4L, finalSeed=4L,
                                  linkage=0.5, kappa=35L)

sum.cl<-summary(cluster.annot)
head(sum.cl)
##   Cluster Enrichment Members
## 1       1  17.552546       6
## 2       2   9.149228      16
## 3       3   6.289612      12
## 4       4   5.121968      10
## 5       5   4.636306       5
## 6       6   4.535552      29
cluster.of.interest<-sum.cl%>%top_n(5, Enrichment)
cl_df_complete<-NULL
for (coi in cluster.of.interest$Cluster){
  l<-(cluster.annot@cluster[[coi]]$Members)
  cl.df<-t(as.data.frame(t(as.data.frame(l))))
  cl.df<-as.data.frame(cl.df)
  cl.df$clusterno<-coi
  cl.df$EnrichScore<-cluster.annot@cluster[[coi]]$EnrichmentScore
  cl_df_complete<-rbind(cl_df_complete, cl.df)
}

cl_df_complete$Count<-as.numeric(as.character(cl_df_complete$Count))
cl_df_complete$clusterno<-ordered(cl_df_complete$clusterno)
cl_df_complete$alpha<-ave(cl_df_complete$Count, cl_df_complete$clusterno, FUN=seq_along)
cl_df_complete$clusterinfo<-paste("Cluster:", cl_df_complete$clusterno, " Enrichment Score: ", round(cl_df_complete$EnrichScore,2), sep = " ")
cl_df_complete$TermInfo<-gsub("^.*~", "", cl_df_complete$Term)


cl_df_complete$Category<-ordered(cl_df_complete$Category, levels = c("GOTERM_CC_FAT", "GOTERM_BP_FAT", "GOTERM_MF_FAT", "UP_KEYWORDS"),
                                 labels = c("GO Cellular Component", "GO Biological Process", "GO Molecular Function", "UniProt Keyword"))
